Afiq scripts the copy, edits highlight reels, and keeps the crew’s tone sharp across newsletters and socials.
Aida fronts mobility labs and helps runners decode recovery metrics so they can stand at the line fresh and confident.
Amin pairs data with fieldwork, shaping programming, risk management, and partnerships so every session hits strategic goals without losing its pulse.
Builds operational dashboards for every block
Amir maps out weekend hikings with leave-no-trace lessons and beginner-friendly pacing on the climbs.
Arbee keeps the club fiscals in stride, managing budgets, sponsorship flows, and transparent reporting so every ringgit fuels runners and community.
Burhan leads back-to-back looped trail LSDs, stacking vert, fueling cues, and crew accountability on every climb.
Debb drills posture, footstrike, and breathing mechanics, delivering micro feedback that refines every runner’s form.
Debb documents every decision, turns ideas into processes, and keeps the crew compliant—from registrations and permits to session briefs and media releases.
Leads the club’s archival and content pipeline
Farid scripts long run progressions, balancing nutrition stops and conversation pace to keep everyone stacking volume.
Hana introduces flora facts and breathing drills, making every hike a reset for runners and their families.
Haneem manages trail sweeps, effort checks, and mental reps so the pack stays locked through technical terrain.
Haris stitches strength blocks into the weekly calendar, anchoring runners with cues on muscle activation and mobility.
Hatib architects periodised training blocks, balancing strength, tempo, and recovery so the crew hits racing form on schedule.
Ijlal translates performance data into punchy interval blocks, keeping runners activated with smart drills and tempo finishes.
Izzat manages the mid-pack, reading traffic flow and pace checks so the crew glides through KL nights with confidence.
Jo anchors hydration support and cadence cues mid-run, keeping every pack locked into conversational pace and prepared for progression blocks.
Johan keeps the peloton tidy, calling out pace cues, traffic alerts, and energy checks every kilometer.
Ken handles gradient prep, layering strength cues with downhill control so the crew stays quick and injury-free.
Liyana scouts new routes around Selangor weekly, blending runnable climbs with teachable moments on footwork and safety.
Malik handles strength blocks, hill repeats, and gear checks so the ultra crew stays ready for huge vert weeks.
Marni powers logistics—from permits to hydration tables—ensuring every division has the checklists, comms, and volunteers it needs to execute.
Nadia choreographs city loops that stitch KL landmarks with safe crossings, keeping night runs smooth and cinematic.
Nisa captures the club heartbeat, directing photo stories and powering launch reels for every big block.
Salma dials hydration plans and teaches micro-interval cues so runners learn how to finish strong on patient miles.
Host, Fuel for Miles micro sessions
Suri plans brutal back-to-back mileage weekends and coaches mental reps for long solo efforts.
Syafiq engineers every Tuesday Speed Work session, dialing in paces and recoveries so the crew can stack quick turnover without burning out.
Syamil curates city grids that weave landmarks, safe crossings, and pace resets so every urban loop lands cinematic and safe.
Syed launched KJ Run Club from neighbourhood loops and now steers the crew’s direction, governance, and partnerships while keeping the culture grounded in community.
Co-founded KJRC and led its 2024 registration
Yan programs Sunday LSD loops with layered mileage and reset segments so the crew keeps stacking aerobic strength without burnout.
